    <h1>Legacy code and features</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>eZ Publish 5 has a strong focus on backwards compatibility and t=
hus lets you reuse code you might have written for 4.x, including templates=
 and modules.</p>=20
<div class=3D"aui-message hint shadowed information-macro">=20
<p class=3D"title">Hint</p>=20
<span class=3D"aui-icon icon-hint">Icon</span>=20
<div class=3D"message-content">=20
<p>Read&nbsp;<a href=3D"/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3D12125336">Intro for=
 eZ Publish 4.x/3.x developers</a> to have an overview of common concepts a=
nd terminology changes.</p>=20
</div>=20
</div>=20
<p><style type=3D"text/css">/*<![CDATA[*/
